                <h1>Understanding John Proctor: A Tragic Hero of "The Crucible"</h1>
                <p>John Proctor is a central character in Arthur Miller's play "The Crucible." A tragic hero and farmer in Salem, he struggles with his guilt and the moral dilemmas of the witch trials. Proctor's fight against hysteria and his quest for integrity highlight themes of redemption, honesty, and the consequences of personal choices, making him a compelling figure in American literature.</p>
